radiographic_examinations.findings: Atelectasis at the lung bases; 3.0-cm septated hypodense lesion in segment IV of the liver likely consistent with a septated cyst; 0.9-cm hypodense lesion in the left kidney likely representing a simple cyst; thickened appendix measuring 8 mm with surrounding fat stranding; mild thickening of the cecal wall at the appendiceal orifice; multiple diverticula noted in the sigmoid colon.
